# NINE20 Official Website - Cursor Rules

## Context

NINE20 is a solo AI startup making AI (Claude, GPT, Gemini) context accessible to non-technical users. The fortune-telling app (사주920 / KRFortuneTeller920) is just the first product. Goal: launch a new AI service monthly. Don't make the site fortune-telling focused.

## Stack

Next.js 16 (App Router, Turbopack) + React 19 + TypeScript 5 (strict) + Tailwind CSS v4 (`@theme inline`, no config file) + Framer Motion 12+ + Lucide React + i18n via Dictionary pattern + Middleware (negotiator).

## Conventions

### Must Follow
- All user-facing text lives in `src/dictionaries/{ko,en}.json`. No hardcoded strings.
- Components receive `dict: Dictionary` prop for translated text.
- Use `"use client"` only when client interactivity is needed.
- `Header`/`Footer` need both `dict` and `lang` props. Other sections need `dict` only.

### Route Params (Next.js 16)
Params are `Promise<{ lang: string }>`. Always await then cast:
```ts
const { lang: rawLang } = await params;
const lang = rawLang as Locale;
const dict = await getDictionary(lang);
```

### Tailwind CSS v4
- Colors defined as CSS custom properties in `src/app/globals.css` `@theme inline` block.
- No `tailwind.config.ts`. Edit globals.css to add/modify colors.
- Key colors: `midnight`, `neon-purple`, `neon-blue`, `neon-cyan`, `text-primary`, `text-secondary`, `text-muted`, `border`
- Utilities: `.gradient-text`, `.glow-purple`, `.glow-border`, `.bg-grid`

### Framer Motion
- Use `as const` on variant objects.
- Ease values: `"easeOut" as const` (strict type requirement).

### File Structure
```
src/
├── lib/i18n.ts              # Locale type & config
├── lib/getDictionary.ts     # Dictionary loader & type
├── dictionaries/{ko,en}.json
├── components/              # Shared components
└── app/
    ├── globals.css           # Tailwind v4 theme
    ├── layout.tsx            # Root pass-through
    ├── page.tsx              # / → /ko redirect
    └── [lang]/
        ├── layout.tsx        # HTML shell + metadata
        ├── page.tsx          # Main landing
        ├── about/page.tsx
        └── blog/page.tsx
```

### Adding Pages
1. Create folder/page.tsx under `app/[lang]/`
2. Add text keys to both `ko.json` and `en.json`
3. Handle async params + Locale cast
4. Include Header/Footer with dict + lang props

### Adding Languages
1. Add to `locales` array in `src/lib/i18n.ts`
2. Create `src/dictionaries/{locale}.json`
3. Register loader in `src/lib/getDictionary.ts`

## Gotchas
- Node.js 24: module issues → `rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json && npm install`
- SSG via `generateStaticParams` — add static params for new dynamic routes.
- Fonts: Inter (Google Fonts) + Pretendard (jsDelivr), loaded in `[lang]/layout.tsx` head.
